A CSS selector is used to target HTML elements so you can apply styles to them.

| Selector Type      | Example                | Targets                                 |
| ------------------ | ---------------------- | --------------------------------------- |
| **Universal**      | `*`                    | All elements                            |
| **Element**        | `p`                    | All `<p>` tags                          |
| **Class**          | `.box`                 | Elements with `class="box"`             |
| **ID**             | `#main`                | Element with `id="main"`                |
| **Group**          | `h1, h2`               | All `<h1>` and `<h2>` elements          |
| **Descendant**     | `div p`                | All `<p>` inside `<div>`                |
| **Child**          | `ul > li`              | Direct `<li>` children of `<ul>`        |
| **Attribute**      | `input[type="text"]`   | `<input>` with type="text"              |
| **Pseudo-class**   | `a:hover`              | `<a>` elements when hovered             |
| **Pseudo-element** | `p::before`, `::after` | Parts of elements (before, after, etc.) |
